Active range of movement (AROM) [14]: The AROM of the affected digit(s) will be measured with a finger goniometer according to a standardised protocol. The total active motion (TAM) will be calculated as the total active flexion of the proximal interphalangeal joint (PIPj) and distal interphalangeal joint (DIPj) motion in a composite fist position minus the extension deficit. The Strickland score will then be calculated from this measurement\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
